Angular Environment
===========================
-CDN  : online link ref 
	<script href="....."  />
 	
-CLI  :
	 enterprise application 
	
Required Software:
	-NodeJs 
		V8 + 
		V8.11
		https://nodejs.org/en/download/

	
	-AngularCLI
		$node -v
		$npm install -g @angular/cli 


	-Editor/IDE (integrated development env.)
		-VSCode  : free
		-Sublime : paid for commm.
		-VisualStudio: paid for comm.
		etc.

		https://code.visualstudio.com/download




Open console/Terminal in VSCode
============
1. Go to view menu and click on open integrated terminal 
$dir 					: show list of files and folder
$node -v   				: show version of nodejs
$npm install -g @angular/cli		: install angular clid (node package manager)

--create angular project
$ng new project-name		 : create new project
$cd project-name		: change directory 
$ng serve			: to build and run the project
	default port is : 
		https://localhost:4200
	
$ng serve --o		or open 
			: to build , run and open the browser 


	
	
-Angular App/Project Structure and Life Cycle
==============================
1. index.html
2. main.ts
3. app.module.ts
4. app.component.ts		     : selector 
		-app.component.html  : template / view 
		-app.component.css   : style 	
		


Create new component
----------------
$ng generate component mypage
or
$ng g c mypage
	mypage.component.html		: VIEW 
	mypage.component.css
	mypage.component.spec.ts : testing
	mypage.component.ts 		: CODE BEHIND 
					-selector 
					app-mypage 

	**add selector in app.component.html file 
	


ctrl+c : to terminate ther terminal 



	




